{
  "texts": [
    "In the endless variety of contexts and interests, no two meanings are ever exactly the same.",
    "Rarely is the same sentence or sequence of sentences written twice.",
    "Never do two pieces of text mean exactly the same thing from one writer to the next or one reader to the next (Cope and Kalantzis 2020: 68-72).",
    "This is precisely where first generation, symbolic and logic-based AI came unstuck in its attempts to base its processes in elementary, universal, generalizable rules of language (Cope cite re Chomsky).",
    "And this is where Generative AI excels-its foundational corpus is the endless of variation of written texts and the near infinity of their contexts and purposes even though the technology itself has no intrinsic sense of this."
  ]
}